## ğŸ—‚ Database & Media Files

This project includes a SQLite database (db.sqlite3) with demo users, preloaded products, and sample orders to facilitate testing and exploration.

The media/ folder contains all the images used for products, carousels, and other site visualsâ€”making it easy to view the full app experience after cloning, with no need for manual data input.


## âœ… Running Locally

Clone the repository:

- git clone https://github.com/LisandroLeone1/React-ecommerce
- cd React-ecommerce

Set up the backend (Django):

- cd backend
- python -m venv .venv
- source .venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate

- pip install -r requirements.txt

- python manage.py migrate         # Run migrations
- python manage.py createsuperuser  # (Optional) Create superuser
- python manage.py runserver       # Start the server

Set up the frontend (React):

- cd front
- npm install
- npm run dev

